bitions%20beyond%20cramming%20for%20the%20SATs%20and%20competing%20with%20his%20classmates%20to%20get%20into%20a%20top%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Taylor%20managed%20to%20land%20a%20six-figure%20job%20as%20a%20coder.%20He%20had%20taught%20himself%20coding%20years%20before%20and%20had%20built%20a%20body%20of%20work%20through%20freelance%20jobs%20and%20side%20projects.%20Eventually%2C%20one%20of%20his%20contacts%20recommended%20him%20for%20a%20gig%20building%20classified%20technology%20for%20the%20Defense%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Taylor%2C%20whose%20great-grandfather%20worked%20on%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%20was%20always%20interested%20in%20nuclear%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2025%2C%20his%20biggest%20venture%20yet%2C%20Valar%20Atomics%2C%20emerged%20from%20stealth%20earlier%20last%20week.%20The%20company%20is%20backed%20by%20a%20team%20of%2035%20nuclear%20experts%20and%20%2421%20million%20in%20funding.%20Taylor%20says%20it%20aims%20to%20make%20nuclear%20energy%20more%20affordable%20%E2%80%94%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20for%20space%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22027b18e5-cc14-4c27-9db5-662e28863fb7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20motto%3A%20cheaper%2C%20faster%2C%20better%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EValar%20aims%20to%20revamp%20the%20way%20nuclear%20reactors%20are%20deployed%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20solve%20the%20problem%20of%20scaling%20them.%20Typical%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20can%20take%20five%20years%20or%20more%20to%20construct.%20In%20Valar's%20view%2C%20that's%20akin%20to%20building%20reactors%20like%20%26quot%3Bartisanal%20cheese.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223360%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Valar%20Atomics%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b6b52deb4be2fff9a513ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EValar%20Atomics%20aims%20to%20build%20%26quot%3Bgigasites%26quot%3B%20to%20deploy%20cheap%20energy.%3Cp%3EDay%20One%20Ventures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20solve%20that%20problem%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20company%20plans%20to%20develop%20what%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3Bgigasites%2C%26quot%3B%20creating%20and%20installing%20thousands%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fthe-us-is-betting-big-on-small-nuclear-reactors-1033164872%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%2C%20modular%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20high-temperature%20gas%20reactors%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20modular%20reactors%2C%20or%20SMRs%2C%20generally%20have%20a%20maximum%20output%20of%20300%20megawatts%20compared%20to%20large%20nuclear%20reactors%2C%20which%20can%20generate%20over%201%2C000%20megawatts.%20Collectively%2C%20though%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20SMRs%20at%20a%20gigasite%20could%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eproduce%20thousands%20of%20times%20the%20energy%20of%20a%20typical%20nuclear%20power%20plant%2C%20according%20to%20Valar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20allows%20you%20to%20produce%20very%20cheap%20energy%20because%20all%20of%20the%20complexity%20is%20already%20dealt%20with%20on%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20reactors%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20distributing%20power%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodernize-us-electric-grid-what-it-will-take-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrid%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20network%20that%20delivers%20electricity%20from%20power%20plants%20to%20homes%20and%20businesses%20%E2%80%94Valar%20plans%20to%20directly%20supply%20power%20to%20customers%20that%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20it%2C%20like%20data%20centers%2C%20green%20steel%20plants%2C%20and%20hydrogen%20production%20facilities%2C%20by%20building%20the%20sites%20right%20next%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%E2%80%8AThe%20grid%20is%20actually%20not%20a%20very%20good%20customer%20for%20nuclear%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%20It%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20your%20reactors%20to%20essentially%20be%20spread%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201c68232-9071-4a7c-8047-bfaf035006c8%5C%22%3EThe%20rise%20of%20the%20small%20modular%20reactor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20image%20of%20X%20Energy's%20XE-100%20nuclear%20reactors%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670fe38e3f2165d716e1eccd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EX%20Energy's%20XE-100%20nuclear%20reactors%20can%20be%20scaled%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bfour-pack%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20company.%3Cp%3EX%20Energy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESMRs%20have%20gained%20momentum%20as%20a%20cheaper%2C%20greener%2C%20and%20faster%20alternative%20to%20traditional%20nuclear%20reactors.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20a%20number%20of%20SMR%20companies%20have%20emerged%20with%20plans%20to%20bring%20their%20first%20reactors%20online%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOklo%2C%20backed%20by%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20is%20developing%20small%20reactors%20that%20run%20on%20nuclear%20waste.%20Oklo%20aims%20to%20deploy%20its%20first%20one%20in%202027.%20X-Energy%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20Amazon%20invested%20%24500%20million%20%E2%80%94%20aims%20to%20bring%20over%205%20gigawatts%20of%20power%20online%20through%20SMRs%20by%202039.%20Kairos%20Power%20also%20signed%20an%20agreement%20with%20Google%20to%20provide%20energy%20from%20its%20SMRs%2C%20with%20plans%20to%20bring%20its%20first%20reactor%20online%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20critics%20of%20SMRs%20argue%20that%20they%20should%20not%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20silver%20bullet%20for%20the%20problems%20that%20plague%20traditional%20reactors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202024%20report%20from%20the%20Institute%20for%20Energy%20Economics%20and%20Financial%20Analysis%20found%20that%20SMRs%20are%20still%20%26quot%3Btoo%20expensive%2C%20too%20slow%20to%20build%2C%20and%20too%20risky%26quot%3B%20to%20meaningfully%20transition%20us%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20the%20coming%2010%20to%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20radioactive%20waste%20produced%20by%20these%20reactors.%20A%202022%20study%20from%20Stanford%20and%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia%20found%20that%20SMRs%20generated%20more%20radioactive%20waste%20by%20%26quot%3Bfactors%20of%202%20to%2030%26quot%3B%20than%20large-scale%20reactors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EValar%20argues%20that%20its%20gigasite%20model%20tackles%20the%20challenges%20of%20cost%20and%20speed%20by%20enabling%20it%20to%20deploy%20reactors%20to%20achieve%20economies%20of%20scale%20rapidly.%20With%20regard%20to%20safety%2C%20the%20company%20points%20to%20its%20use%20of%20tri-structural%20isotropic%20particle%20fuel%2C%20a%20heat-resistant%20nuclear%20fuel%20made%20from%20a%20combination%20of%20uranium%2C%20carbon%2C%20and%20oxygen.%20TRISO%2C%20as%20this%20fuel%20is%20more%20commonly%20known%2C%20generates%20more%20nuclear%20waste%2C%20but%20Valar%20claims%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bgood%20at%20encapsulating%20the%20nuclear%20waste%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20it%20highly%20resistant%20to%20spreading%2C%20minimizing%20environmental%20impact%2C%20and%20preventing%20misuse%20by%20bad%20actors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETRISO%20is%20also%20being%20tested%20by%20Kairos%20Power%20and%20X-Energy%2C%20which%20is%20building%20a%20dedicated%20fuel%20fabrication%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9b51f7b-0f28-49e3-a42a-7fc29ad0b1f4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFuel%20and%20ambition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20a%20young%20startup%2C%20Valar%20also%20has%20big%20plans%20to%20fuel%20the%20world%20with%20synthetic%20fuels%20that%20are%20cheaper%20than%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20it%20has%20pioneered%20a%20process%20for%20developing%20alternative%20hydrocarbon%20fuels%20that%20can%20replace%20the%20traditional%20fuel%20used%20in%20aviation%2C%20vehicles%2C%20and%20military%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20begins%20with%20the%20company's%20reactors%2C%20which%20%E2%80%94%20once%20up%20and%20running%20%E2%80%94%20will%20generate%20heat%20at%20temperatures%20exceeding%20900%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20or%20over%201%2C650%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EValar%20aims%20to%20use%20this%20heat%20to%20power%20a%20thermochemical%20process%20that%20splits%20water%20into%20its%20component%20atoms%3A%20hydrogen%20and%20oxygen.%20The%20hydrogen%20will%20then%20be%20combined%20with%20captured%20carbon%20dioxide%20through%20a%20collection%20of%20chemical%20reactions%20to%20create%20carbon-neutral%20synthetic%20fuels%20because%20no%20new%20carbon%20is%20extracted%20from%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%E2%80%8AYou%20can%20sell%20the%20hydrogen%20itself%2C%20right%2C%20which%20is%20a%20big%20market%2C%20but%20you%20can%20also%20create%2C%20synthetic%20fuel%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%20%26quot%3B%E2%80%8AWe%20can%20make%20jet%20fuel%2C%20diesel%2C%20gasoline.%20We%20can%20make%20all%20of%20our%20hydrocarbons%20that%20the%20world%20relies%20on%20today%2C%20and%20we%20can%20make%20them%20carbon%20neutral.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EValar's%20first%20reactor%20will%20launch%20in%20the%20Philippines%2C%20where%20it%20has%20secured%20a%20research%20contract%20for%20an%20advanced%20reactor%20from%20the%20Philippines%20Nuclear%20Research%20Institute.%20This%20follows%20the%20signing%20of%20the%20123%20Agreement%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20Philippines%20in%202023%2C%20which%20establishes%20a%20framework%20for%20enhanced%20nuclear%20cooperation%20between%20the%20countries%2C%20including%20technical%20exchanges%2C%20scientific%20research%2C%20and%20safeguards%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20a%20prototype%2C%20Valar%20will%20simulate%20its%20first%20reactor%2C%20Ward%20One%2C%20to%20test%20and%20gather%20data%20on%20its%20efficacy.%20Taylor%20did%20not%20specify%20how%20long%20it%20will%20take%20to%20move%20through%20the%20licensing%20process%20and%20fully%20get%20the%20reactor%20running%20in%20the%20Philippines%20but%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20move%20really%20fast.%26quot%3B%20Eventually%2C%20Taylor%20wants%20to%20bring%20Valar's%20technology%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2219852181-8184-43d4-a4e9-b479f7d602d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20new%20nuclear%20era%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20believes%20this%20is%20an%20opportune%20moment%20for%20nuclear%20energy%20in%20the%20United%20States%20as%20public%20sentiment%20has%20shifted%20in%20the%20past%20several%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPublic%20opinion%20about%20nuclear%20is%20actually%20very%20generational%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYoung%20people%20and%2C%20and%20I%20really%20mean%2C%20honestly%2C%20anyone%20under%2050%20are%20very%2C%20very%20pro-nuclear.%26quot%3B%20Now%20that%20they're%20in%20positions%20of%20authority%2C%20Taylor%20anticipates%20that%20we'll%20see%20%26quot%3Brapid%20regulatory%20change.%26quot%3B%20A%202024%20poll%20of%20430%20first-generation%20voters%20conducted%20by%20America%20in%20One%20Room%2C%20organized%20in%20part%20by%20Stanford%20University%2C%20found%20that%20four%20in%20five%20supported%20%26quot%3Bnew%20generation%26quot%3B%20nuclear%20energy%20to%20supplement%20renewable%20power%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22452%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nuclear%20Reactors.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf7a9db8b41a9673f91699%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22339%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20traditional%20nuclear%20reactor%20plant.%3Cp%3EAnton%20Petrus%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20support%20from%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20which%20needs%20more%20energy%20for