efore%20each%20one-on-one%20meeting%20with%20her%20manager%2C%20Bonacolta%20spent%20one%20hour%20preparing%20a%20%26quot%3Bpre-read.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPre-reads%20included%20weekly%20wins%2C%20upcoming%20tasks%2C%20and%20new%20ideas%2C%20helping%20increase%20her%20visibility%20at%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jade%20Bonacolta%2C%20a%2031-year-old%20based%20in%20Miami%20who%20began%20her%20career%20at%20LinkedIn%20and%20is%20now%20head%20of%20North%20American%20marketing%20at%20Google.%20Her%20employment%20and%20promotion%20history%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20from%20Columbia%20University%20in%202015%2C%20I%20landed%20a%20job%20at%20LinkedIn%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20six%20and%20a%20half%20years%20I%20was%20at%20LinkedIn%20before%20joining%20Google%20in%202022%2C%20I%20was%20promoted%20five%20times%2C%20beginning%20as%20an%20associate%20in%20the%20Business%20Leadership%20Program%20and%20leaving%20as%20the%20head%20of%20marketing%20for%20enterprise%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20my%20promotions%20came%20from%20the%20way%20I%20handled%20my%20one-on-one%20meetings%20with%20my%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205ece9d4-50d3-4d1b-b232-255e4d23ba47%5C%22%3EPreparing%20pre-reads%20for%20my%20one-on-ones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20go%20into%20one-on-ones%20taking%20a%20more%20passive%20approach%2C%20expecting%20their%20manager%20to%20present%20to%20them%20and%20tell%20them%20what%20to%20do.%20But%20managers%20often%20have%20teams%20of%20five%20or%20more%20people%2C%20so%20having%20weekly%20meetings%20with%20each%20of%20them%20can%20be%20a%20lot%20to%20juggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20noticed%20that%20my%20first%20manager%20would%20generally%20ask%20me%20the%20same%20things%20in%20every%20call%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BHow%20did%20this%20week%20go%3F%20What%20are%20you%20working%20on%20next%20week%20and%20where%20do%20you%20need%20help%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20more%20proactive%20and%20make%20those%20meetings%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20spending%20an%20hour%20beforehand%20writing%20up%20what%20I%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bpre-read.%26quot%3B%20I%20would%20draft%20a%20simple%20email%20with%20three%20sections%3A%20what%20went%20well%20for%20me%20this%20week%2C%20what%20I'm%20focusing%20on%20next%20week%2C%20and%20one%20new%20idea%20or%20interesting%20innovation%20to%20suggest%20for%20our%20team.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20send%20it%20to%20my%20manager%20before%20we%20met%20and%20bring%20my%20copy%20to%20the%20meeting%20to%20help%20guide%20our%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20manager%20told%20me%20he%20found%20the%20pre-reads%20incredibly%20helpful%3B%20they%20made%20our%20conversations%20far%20more%20productive%20and%20helped%20him%20feel%20completely%20aware%20of%20my%20work.%20He%20found%20the%20format%20so%20useful%20that%20he%20asked%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20team%20members%20to%20follow%20the%20strategy%20for%20their%20one-on-ones%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228017c3cd-d436-4a74-b49c-11036f1b3c2d%5C%22%3E3%20things%20that%20make%20an%20effective%20pre-read%20before%20a%201%3A1%20meeting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226921a8c7-167d-47ed-bcfd-7dabdb49f2be%5C%22%3E1.%20What%20went%20well%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20I%20created%20a%20%26quot%3Bwins%26quot%3B%20folder%2C%20and%20every%20time%20I%20had%20a%20win%20throughout%20my%20week%2C%20I%20would%20add%20it%20to%20the%20folder.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%2C%20when%20working%20with%20the%20sales%20team%2C%20I%20received%20an%20email%20from%20one%20of%20the%20leaders%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20so%20impressed%20with%20the%20questions%20you%20asked%20my%20team%20and%20the%20way%20you%20provided%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20email%20would%20go%20straight%20into%20the%20wins%20folder.%20I%20would%20then%20pull%20from%20that%20folder%20when%20making%20my%20pre-read%20email%20to%20my%20manager.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20understood%20that%20I%20could%20be%20doing%20the%20best%20work%20in%20the%20world%2C%20but%20it%20didn't%20matter%20if%20the%20right%20people%20didn't%20know%20about%20it%3B%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20promoted%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20be%20visible.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20also%20save%20all%20of%20my%20wins%20in%20a%20document%20and%20share%20it%20with%20my%20manager%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20write%20my%20performance%20review%20and%20build%20a%20case%20for%20my%20promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291594f78-c4f0-429d-9e4c-996c523b9cd4%5C%22%3E2.%20What%20I'm%20working%20on%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20are%20often%20expected%20to%20tell%20their%20employees%20what%20they%20should%20be%20working%20on.%20However%2C%20it%20can%20also%20be%20helpful%20and%20beneficial%20if%20the%20employees%20show%20proactiveness.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20sharing%20what%20I%20did%20the%20week%20before%2C%20I%20would%20then%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHere's%20what%20I%20think%20I%20should%20work%20on%20next%20week.%26quot%3B%20Some%20of%20these%20were%20ongoing%20projects%2C%20while%20others%20were%20new%20initiatives%20I%20was%20introducing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20projects%2C%20I%20had%20a%20pretty%20strong%20instinct%20on%20the%20direction%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20my%20career%2C%20and%20I%20made%20the%20promotion%20I%20wanted%20clear%20to%20my%20manager.%20I%20asked%20them%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20there%20any%20projects%20I%20could%20work%20on%20that%20allow%20me%20to%20start%20building%20those%20skills%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20tried%20to%20anticipate%20where%20I%20might%20need%20my%20manager's%20help.%20I'd%20ask%20myself%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20could%20possibly%20go%20wrong%20next%20week%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BWhich%20person