or-renters-where-apartments-rents-are-falling-cheaper-2024-2%5C%22%3Ein%20February%202024%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20renters%20shouldn't%20count%20on%20more%20affordable%20apartments%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20opposite%20may%20be%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack-to-back%20years%20of%20rent%20sliding%20from%20January%20to%20February%20could%20simply%20mean%20that%20more%20leases%20end%20in%20the%20first%20month%20of%20the%20year.%20A%20smaller%20pool%20of%20tenants%20deciding%20to%20move%20or%20re-up%20could%20translate%20to%20softer%20rental%20demand%2C%20which%20would%20temporarily%20cause%20apartment%20prices%20to%20pull%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that%20relief%20likely%20won't%20last%20long%2C%20as%20price%20growth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-best-cities-for-renters-rent-growth-inflation-report-2024-3%5C%22%3Eresumed%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20taking%20off%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffalling-rent-apartment-price-locations-us-housing-market-inflation-zumper-2024-6%5C%22%3Elate%20spring%20and%20early%20summer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Either%20way%2C%20the%20difference%20in%20median%20rents%20at%20the%20national%20level%20was%20just%20a%20few%20dollars%20in%20either%20direction%2C%20which%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20a%20major%20tipping%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRents%20staying%20pretty%20flat%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%20is%20pretty%20on%20trend%20with%20this%20time%20of%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWinter%20months%20see%20lower%20rental%20demand%2C%20so%20even%20as%20some%20leases%20end%2C%20limited%20competition%20keeps%20prices%20relatively%20stable%20until%20the%20busier%20spring%20and%20summer%20seasons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E12%20top%20cities%20for%20deal-minded%20renters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApartment%20prices%20in%20the%20100%20largest%20US%20cities%20that%20Zumper%20tracks%20each%20month%20fore