0on%20the%20inferred%20probabilities%20from%20markets%2C%20investors%20expect%20to%20see%20two%20cuts%20from%20the%20Fed%20in%202025.%20But%20as%20the%20true%20picture%20of%20the%20economy%20comes%20into%20view%2C%20I%20would%20expect%20a%20couple%20more%20than%20that%20before%20the%20year%20is%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20warning%20that%20a%20crash%20was%20just%20around%20the%20corner%2C%20economists%20and%20Wall%20Street%20analysts%20have%20largely%20abandoned%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-us-recession-2025-outlook-zero-percent-chance-worry-about-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eidea%20of%20a%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20meaningful%20growth%20slowdown%20hitting%20the%20US.%20But%20as%20the%20core%20parts%20of%20the%20engine%20slow%20and%20the%20Fed%20sits%20back%20and%20does%20nothing%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20noticeably%20weaker%20economy%20are%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20reasonable%20read%20of%20the%20data%20points%20to%20a%20clear%20cooling%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%20Sure%2C%20GDP%20growth%20in%202024%20came%20in%20at%20a%20respectable%202.5%25%2C%20but%20that's%20down%20from%203%25%20in%202023.%20And%20the%20way%20that%20the%20US%20arrived%20at%20that%20growth%20was%20not%20especially%20encouraging.%20Household%20consumption%20and%20government%20investment%20accounted%20for%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20growth%20last%20year%2C%20while%20gross%20private%20domestic%20investment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20tracks%20companies%20putting%20money%20into%20their%20businesses%20and%20the%20amount%20spent%20on%20building%20new%20homes%2C%20apartments%2C%20and%20other%20structures%20%E2%80%94%20was%20a%20modest%20drag.%20Given%20the%20narrow%20composition%20of%20growth%2C%20it%20stands%20to%20reason%20that%20if%20consumer%20spending%20and%20government%20investment%20moderate%2C%20the%20economy%20will%2C%20too.%20The%20case%20for%20a%20slowdown%20in%20both%20categories%20is%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20outlook%20for%20consumption%20boils%20down%20to%20incomes%20%E2%80%94%20people%20can%20spend%20more%20money%20only%20if%20they%20have%20more%20money%20coming%20in.%20And%20it's%20clear%20that%20income%20growth%20is%20easing%20as%20the%20labor%20markets%20cool.%20The%20percentage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraises-promotions-harder-get-low-quit-rates-interest-rates-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20quitting%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20hit%20fresh%20lows%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20and%20as%20quits%20decline%2C%20so%20too%20does%20wage%20growth.%20This%20makes%20sense%3A%20When%20workers%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20leave%20their%20jobs%2C%20employers%20feel%20less%20need%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpromotions-salaries-cut-career-advancement-stagnation-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egive%20them%20raises%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20keep%20them%20around%2C%20which%20shifts%20power%20from%20employees%20to%20employers.%20And%20as%20incomes%20slow%2C%20so%20will%20consumption.%20In%20fact%2C%20we've%20already%20seen%20some%20of%20this%20decline%3A%20Inflation-adjusted%20incomes%20net%20of%20transfer%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20a%20proxy%20for%20people's%20paychecks%20with%20government%20payments%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicaid%20stripped%20out%20%E2%80%94%20was%20a%20full%20percentage%20point%20below%20the%20pace%20of%20consumption.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20personal%20savings%20rate%20(a%20measure%20of%20the%20percentage%20that%20people%20are%20setting%20aside)%20fell%20to%203.8%25%20from%204.4%25%20in%202023%2C%20suggesting%20that%20Americans%20were%20dipping%20into%20their%20reserves%20to%20keep%20the%20spending%20going.%20But%20there's%20a%20limit%20to%20how%20much%20consumers%20can%20draw%20down%20their%20savings%20to%20fuel%20buying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%2