per.dwcdn.net%2FlmX0z%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20number%20of%20unsold%20homes%20sitting%20on%20the%20market%20is%20on%20the%20rise%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22487%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20slowing%20of%20growth%20would%20have%20serious%20consequences%20for%20Americans.%20One%20clear%20downside%20is%20a%20likely%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20people%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20Despite%20strong%20growth%20in%20both%202023%20and%202024%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20still%20rose%200.3%20percentage%20points%20in%20each%20of%20those%20years.%20If%20growth%20is%20likely%20to%20slow%20in%202025%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20tough%20leap%20to%20assume%20that%20unemployment%20will%20keep%20rising.%20If%20there's%20more%20slack%20in%20the%20job%20market%2C%20it's%20not%20hard%20to%20see%20incomes%20slowing%20further%20and%20a%20negative%20feedback%20loop%20kicking%20in%2C%20weighing%20on%20household%20spending%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2C%20of%20course%2C%20ways%20to%20blunt%20or%20even%20avoid%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20impacts%20of%20this%20slowing.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20important%20routes%20to%20support%20the%20economy%20is%20for%20the%20Fed%20to%20start%20cutting%20interest%20rates.%20Making%20debt%20cheaper%20would%20encourage%20businesses%20to%20invest%20or%20hire%2C%20while%20providing%20some%20cushion%20for%20household%20balance%20sheets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20the%20Fed%20was%20already%20bringing%20down%20its%20key%20rate%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20get%20in%20front%20of%20a%20deeper%20slowdown%20in%20the%20labor%20market.%20And%20the%20reason%20the%20Fed%20hiked%20rates%20in%20the%20first%20place%20%E2%80%94%20inflation%20%E2%80%94%20is%20also%20showing%20continuing%20signs%20of%20progress%20back%20toward%20the%20central%20bank's%20goal%20of%202%25%20year-over-year%20growth.%20While%20the%20most%20recent%20consumer%20price%20index%20inflation%20reading%20was%20a%20little%20hotter%20than%20expected%2C%20the%20Fed's%20preferred%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20inflation%20gauge%20has%20given%20us%20better%20news.%20Core%20PCE%20inflation%2C%20which%20is%20more%20reliable%20because%20it%20has%20a%20much%20larger%20scope%20than%20core%20CPI%2C%20got%20back%20on%20track%20in%20November%20and%20December%20after%20two%20discouraging%20months.%20Most%20of%20the%20shortfall%20in%20core%20inflation%2C%20relative%20to%20the%20Fed's%20target%2C%20is%20in%20housing.%20Given%20the%20aforementioned%20slowdown%20in%20price%20growth%20in%20the%20housing%20market%2C%20it%20stands%20to%20reason%20this%20will%20continue%20easing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20keeping%20up%20its%20rate%20cuts%2C%20however%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-fed-rate-cut-inflation-policy-outlook-job-market-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed%20has%20changed%20course%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20preferring%20a%20more%20reactive%20approach%20to%20the%20data%20on%20the%20chance%20inflation%20surprises%20us%20by%20moving%20up.%20It's%20already%20foolish%20to%20wait%20for%20permission%20from%20the%20data%20before%20moving%20rates%20since%20it%20raises%20the%20chance%20that%20you%20fall%20behind%2C%20but%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20Fed's%20worries%20about%20increased%20inflation%20makes%20even%20less%20sense%20because%20it's%20clear%20that%20this%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20speculation%20on%20what%20the%20new%20administration%20might%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImmediately%20following%20the%20election%2C%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20was%20pretty%20clear%20when%20he%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20incoming%20administration's%20policies.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20guess%2C%20we%20don't%20speculate%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20assume%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20told%20reporters.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rates-federal-reserve-holds-steady-powell-trump-inflation-tariffs-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPowell%20seemed%20to%20have%20changed%20his%20tune%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20people%20did%20take%20a%20very%20preliminary%20step%20and%20start%20to%20incorporate%20highly%20conditional%20estimates%20of%20economic%20effects%20of%20policies%20into%20their%20forecast%20at%20this%20meeting%20and%20said%20so%20in%20the%20meeting%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20during%20a%20press%20conference%20following%20the%20Fed's%20December%20meeting.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20they%20do%20guess%2C%20speculate%2C%20and%20assume.%20How%20convenient!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20address%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%3A%20Donald%20Trump.%20In%20recent%20weeks%2C%20many%20business%20economists%20have%20highlighted%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-dei-tariffs-taxes-business-uncertainty-scaredy-cat-capitalism-anxiety-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euncertainty%20coming%20from%20his%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20his%20chaotic%20approach%20to%20trade%20policy.%20The%20on-again%2C%20off-again%20tariff%20threats%20are%20said%20to%20freeze%20business%20investment%2C%20and%20if%20implemented%2C%20they%20could%20push%20inflation%20back%20up.%20This%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20the%20source%20of%20Powell's%20wait-and-see%20pivot.%20But%20the%20evidence%20for%20a%20real%20effect%20from%20the%20president's%20policies%20is%20weak%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20always%20some%20uncertainty%20when%20power%20changes%20hands%20in%20Washington.%20Consider%20the%20alternative.%20Had%20Kamala%20Harris%20won%20the%20election%2C%20there%20would%20be%20much%20more%20doubt%20about%20whether%20the%202017%20tax%20cuts%2C%20which%20are%20set%20to%20expire%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20would%20be%20extended%20or%20whether%20tax%20rates%20would%20go%20up%20for%20households%20and%20businesses.%20If%20corporate%20taxes%20went%20up%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20a%20wide%20body%20of%20research%20suggests%20that%20those%20increased%20taxes%20would%20likely%20be%20passed%20onto%20consumers.%20Does%20anyone%20seriously%20think%20that%20the%20Fed%20would%20worry%20about%20upside%20risks%20to%20inflation%20from%20corporate%20tax%20pass-through%3F%20No%2C%20the%20Fed%20would%20likely%20be%20eyeing%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20as%20a%20way%20to%20stem%20any%20downside%20growth%20risks%20from%20the%20decreased%20spending%20and%20investment.%20This%20is%20exactly%20why%20it%20is%20so%20irresponsible%20to%20prejudge%20outcomes.%20Follow%20the%20data%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20speculating%20over%20a%20series%20of%20policies%20that%20may%20not%20even%20take%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20me%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20businesses%20are%20willing%20to%20give%20the%20new%20administration%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%20Tariffs%20are%20not%20the%20only%20dimension%20of%20policy.%20Perhaps%20firms%20are%20willing%20to%20tolerate%20some%20short-run%20uncertainty%20around%20tariffs%20if%20it%20implies%20an%20improved%20regulatory%20and%20tax%20backdrop%20down%20the%20road.%20Obviously%2C%20there%20is%20enthusiasm%2C%20for%20example%2C%20for%20a%20lighter-touch%20approach%20to%20financial%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F2iFNu%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Policy%20uncertainty%20and%20CEO%20confidence%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22326%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20is%20also%20not%20the%20only%20source%20of%20uncertainty.%20If%20Congress%20fumbles%20the%20ball%20on%20legislation%2C%20confidence%20could%20stall%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20confidence%20is%20predicated%20on%20the%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act%20being%20extended%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20That%20would%20be%20a%20much%20bigger%20risk%20to%20the%20economic%20outlook%20than%20the%20threat%20of%20tariffs.%20The%20downside%20scenario%20here%20is%20obvious%3A%20Nothing%20of%20substance%20happens%2C%20at%20least%20not%20right%20away%2C%20from%20either%20Congress%20or%20Trump%2C%20but%20the%20Fed%2C%20because%20it%20is%20concerned%20about%20possible%20policies%2C%20decides%20to%20hold%20off%20doing%20anything%20as%20nominal%20growth%20continues%20to%20slow.%20This%20would%20be%20a%20passive%20tightening%20of%20monetary%20policy%2C%20which%20has%20important%20implications%20for%20financial%20market%20investors.%20I%20anticipate%20a%20decline%20in%20longer-term%20interest%20rates%20and%20a%20sell-off%20in%20equity%20prices%20as%20risk%20appetite%20wanes.%20For%20the%20economy%2C%20expect%20conditions%20to%20deteriorate%20in%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20will%20eventually%20come%20around%2C%20cutting%20rates%20to%20support%20growth%2C%20but%20if%20you%20are%20waiting%20for%20the%20bad%20news%20to%20be%20obvious%20before%20doing%20something%2C%20it%20usually%20has%20a%20way%20of%20showing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fneil-dutta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ENeil%20Dutta%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20head%20of%20economics%20at%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-gdp-slowing-down-recession-risk-rising-unemployment-inflation-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740647222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf600069253ccddf97a73e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-economy-gdp-slowing-down-recession-risk-rising-unemployment-inflation-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%